(125, 1, '2025-10-06 18:16:47', '2025-10-06 18:16:47', '<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-text-align-center\">Meet the King</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"33.33%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":72,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-rounded\"><img src=\"https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/31KING-articleLarge.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-72\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"66.66%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Stephen King, often referred to as the <em>Master of Horror</em>, is one of the most prolific and influential writers of modern times. Born on September 21, 1947, in Portland, Maine, King had a difficult childhood after his father abandoned the family when Stephen was only two years old. Raised by his mother, Nellie Ruth Pillsbury King, Stephen and his older brother David moved frequently before eventually settling in Durham, Maine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Kings love for storytelling began at an early age. As a child, he wrote short stories for fun and even submitted some to magazines, though they were often rejected. In high school, he discovered horror and science fiction magazines that inspired him to start experimenting with his own tales of suspense and the supernatural. After graduating from the University of Maine at Orono in 1970 with a degree in English, King worked a series of jobs, including as a teacher and in a laundry, while writing on the side.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Over the decades, King has published more than 60 novels and 200 short stories, many of which have been adapted into movies, miniseries, and TV shows. His works span across horror, fantasy, science fiction, and even crime fiction, proving his versatility as a storyteller.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Today, Stephen King remains one of the worlds most widely read authors, known for his ability to tap into universal fears while also exploring themes of love, memory, childhood, and resilience. His works have sold over 350 million copies worldwide, making him not only a literary icon but also a cultural figure whose influence on popular fiction is undeniable.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">[skb-review]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:block {\"ref\":117} /-->', 'Author Bio', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '35-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-06 18:16:47', '2025-10-06 18:16:47', '', 35, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?p=125', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
