<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Over the decades, King has published more than 60 novels and 200 short stories, many of which have been adapted into movies, miniseries, and TV shows. His works span across horror, fantasy, science fiction, and even crime fiction, proving his versatility as a storyteller.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Today, Stephen King remains one of the worlds most widely read authors, known for his ability to tap into universal fears while also exploring themes of love, memory, childhood, and resilience. His works have sold over 350 million copies worldwide, making him not only a literary icon but also a cultural figure whose influence on popular fiction is undeniable.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">[skb-review]</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":132,\"sizeSlug\":\"medium\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"is-style-rounded\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-medium is-style-rounded\"><img src=\"https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Stephen_King_characters-300x225.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-132\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:block {\"ref\":117} /-->', 'Author Bio', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '35-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-06 21:27:26', '2025-10-06 21:27:26', '', 35, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?p=136', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(137, 1, '2025-10-06 21:31:38', '2025-10-06 21:31:38', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Reading <em>Geralds Game</em> was an intense and unsettling experience that stuck with me long after I finished it. The book dives into fear and trauma in a way that feels deeply personal and psychological rather than purely scary. I found myself constantly on edge, not because of monsters, but because of how real Jessies emotions and struggles felt. Its slower at times, but that pacing makes the moments of realization and horror hit even harder. This isnt an easy or comforting read, but its one that really makes you think and feel every moment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Leaving a Lasting Impact', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leaving-a-lasting-impact', '', '', '2025-10-06 23:58:32', '2025-10-06 23:58:32', '', 0, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=review&#038;p=137', 0, 'review', '', 0),
(138, 1, '2025-10-06 21:34:23', '2025-10-06 21:34:23', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pet Sematary is one of those books that quietly crawls under your skin and stays there. Reading it felt both heartbreaking and horrifying, as King explores grief and the desperate lengths people will go to avoid loss. I found myself deeply unsettled, not just by the supernatural elements, but by how human and believable the emotions were. Its dark, sad, and thought-provoking in a way that few horror novels manage to be. By the end, I wasnt just scared  I was emotionally drained, but in the best possible way.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Deeply Emotional Read', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'deeply-emotional-read', '', '', '2025-10-06 21:34:23', '2025-10-06 21:34:23', '', 0, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=review&#038;p=138', 0, 'review', '', 0),
(139, 1, '2025-10-06 21:35:23', '2025-10-06 21:35:23', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>The Shining</em> is one of those books that completely pulls you into its atmosphere  cold, eerie, and emotionally heavy. Reading it felt like slowly losing your grip on reality right alongside the characters. I was amazed at how King makes the Overlook Hotel itself feel alive, feeding off the fears and weaknesses of the people inside it. The psychological tension builds so naturally that by the end, its impossible to look away. Its a haunting story about isolation, addiction, and family that feels just as powerful as it is terrifying.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'So Chilly', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'so-chilly', '', '', '2025-10-06 21:35:23', '2025-10-06 21:35:23', '', 0, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=review&#038;p=139', 0, 'review', '', 0),
(140, 1, '2025-10-06 21:37:29', '2025-10-06 21:37:29', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Misery</em> is one of the most tense and claustrophobic books Ive ever read. The relationship between Paul Sheldon and Annie Wilkes is both fascinating and terrifying  I could feel the desperation in every scene. What stood out most to me was how real Annie felt; shes not just a villain, shes disturbingly human. The entire story kept me on edge, with moments that made me cringe, flinch, and even laugh nervously. Its a brutal but brilliant look at obsession, control, and creativity under pressure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'More Than a Villian', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'more-than-a-villian', '', '', '2025-10-07 00:01:18', '2025-10-07 00:01:18', '', 0, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=review&#038;p=140', 0, 'review', '', 0),
(141, 1, '2025-10-07 00:00:16', '2025-10-07 00:00:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is a massive and unforgettable story that perfectly captures both childhood wonder and lifelong fear. Reading it felt like revisiting the strange mix of magic and terror that comes with growing up. The bond between the kids  the Losers Club  is what makes the story so powerful, even when the horror becomes overwhelming. King balances moments of heart and hope with scenes that are deeply disturbing and emotional. Its more than just a scary clown story  its about friendship, memory, and the things we cant escape.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'IT Is Spooky Scary', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'it-is-spooky-scary', '', '', '2025-10-07 00:00:16', '2025-10-07 00:00:16', '', 0, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=review&#038;p=141', 0, 'review', '', 0),
(142, 1, '2025-10-07 00:03:39', '2025-10-07 00:03:39', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Misery is the story of an author held captive by a maniacal fan. The setting, for the type of story it is, hidden away in the mountains is perfect. After the main character gets into a car accident and the protagonist is introduced the mood instantly shifted, and had me captivated. The book was an easy, but exciting, story to read. The psychological side of the book was executed brilliantly. I was on the edge of my seat, wondering what horror and gore were to come next for the majority of it. There is flaw in everything, though, and my only grievance in the book was how the protagonist\'s mental illness was portrayed and explored, or lack thereof.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Edge of my Seat', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'edge-of-my-seat', '', '', '2025-10-07 00:03:39', '2025-10-07 00:03:39', '', 0, 'https://brehak.bitlampsites.com/wpd/final/?post_type=review&#038;p=142', 0, 'review', '', 0),
